narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course looks to establish the role of the intellectual in politics by reading some of the key works by public intellectuals in the past century. All of the readings are extremely interesting and the professor is awesome!
If you are interested in Conservative politics, philosophy, or the tradition, then this class is for you. If you find iconic figures interesting, you might also consider this class.

I would definitely recommend this course. Professor Petranovich is awesome and the course material is a grand example of the growing understanding of the intersection of intellectuals and political life.
